                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι"><supplied reason="lost">ἀνέ</supplied><unclear>θ</unclear>ηκε</w> 
                        <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <space atLeast="4" unit="character"/> <orig>α<choice><unclear>μ</unclear><unclear>ν</unclear></choice></orig>
                        <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> a consacré <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> dedicated <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> ha dedicato <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>At line 2, we see the summit of a triangular letter followed by the upper left angle of a mu or nu. It is hence most probable that the first letter 
               was an alpha. This is probably the beginning of a personal name.</p>
